! UUID v7 Plugin

Every new tiddler automatically receives a `c32` field containing a [[UUID v7|https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc9562]] encoded in [[Crockford Base32|https://www.crockford.com/base32.html]] — a globally unique, time-ordered, compact identifier. This ID survives renaming, copying, and cross-wiki migration.

!! Try it

# Create a new tiddler
# Open the fields editor — notice the `c32` field with a value like `01KMNH-72WK-FM8S1A277T55-S8DK`
# The c32 badge at the bottom-right shows the value with its check symbol
# The phrase badge at the bottom-left shows its mnemonic encoding

!! Mnemonic Phrases

Each UUID is encoded as 8 ''adjective noun verb'' triplets. The first three triplets are derived from the timestamp, triplets 4-8 encode the random and fixed bits:

* ''Triplet 1'' — stable for years (adjective ~278 years, noun ~4 years, verb ~50 days)
* ''Triplet 2'' — stable for minutes (adjective ~1.5 days, noun ~34 minutes, verb ~1 minute)
* ''Triplet 3'' — sub-second (adjective ~2 seconds, noun ~32 ms, verb ~1 ms)
* ''Triplet 8'' — lowest 16 bits of the UUID — fully random, unique per tiddler

Example: `metal dog soars, calm seal hunts, ...`

Use the sidebar search tab ''UUID Phrase'' to find tiddlers by phrase words.

!! Filter Operators

Both `c32` and `uuid7` filters have full feature parity — phrase encoding, timestamps, check symbols, validation, and cross-conversion:

|! Filter |! Example |! Reference |
|`c32` |`[get[c32]c32[phrase]]` |[[uuid7/filter-c32]] |
|`uuid7` |`[get[c7]uuid7[phrase]]` |[[uuid7/filter-uuid7]] |
|`uuid7link` |`[<tiddler>uuid7link[]]` |[[uuid7/phrase-links]] |

!! Navigation: c32 and Phrase Links

Open tiddlers by c32 value (full or partial) or phrase words in URL hashes:

```
http://localhost:8080/#01KMNH-72WK-FM8S1A277T55-S8DK
http://localhost:8080/#S8DK
http://localhost:8080/#FM8S1A277T55
http://localhost:8080/#metal+dog+soars,cool+dune+casts
```

Wiki links work the same way: `[[S8DK]]` or `[[metal+dog+soars]]`. Use `;` to open multiple tiddlers in one phrase link. See [[uuid7/crockford32]] and [[uuid7/phrase-links]] for details.

!! Backfill Existing Tiddlers

The plugin can add `c7` and `c32` fields to tiddlers that were created before the plugin was installed. On startup it runs in ''dry-run'' mode by default — check [[_log/backfill-c7]] to see what would change. See [[uuid7/backfill]] for details on how to switch to ''live'' mode.

!! Settings

Configure the plugin in [[$:/ControlPanel]] > Settings > WikiLabs > UUID v7.

